\n\nIn 1950, renowned Bengali director Mrinal Sen made the film "Under The Blue Sky”, which was set during the 1930s, when a strong anti-colonialist sentiment had arisen in India. The film includes a scene with Wang Lu, a Chinese peddler who sells Shandong silk. The scene is remarkable in that the character of Wang Lu is treated with sensitivity -- a rare moment in Indian film history where an ethnic minority is portrayed in a positive light. \nFor us, this song, "O Nodi Re," speaks to the sadness of the Indian Chinese being forced to leave their homes, as well as the tragedy of living under colonialist rule in India. We used this song in the film, weaving it with excerpts from Sen''s film and oral histories told by Indian Chinese.    \n', '2014-03-31 00:00:00', 2000, 25, 2, 7, '河流啊\n我只有一個問題\nOh, river\nI have only one question \n\n河流啊\n我只有一個問題\nOh, river\nI have only one question \n\n你從哪裡來?\n你從不停歇嗎?\nWhere do you come from?\nYou never stop and rest\n\n河流啊\n我只有一個問題\nOh, river\nI have only one question \n\n你從哪裡來?\n你從不停歇嗎?\nWhere do you come from?\nYou never stop and rest\n', '河流啊\n我只有一個問題\nOh, river\nI have only one question \n\n河流啊\n我只有一個問題\nOh, river\nI have only one question \n\n你從哪裡來?\n你從不停歇嗎?\nWhere do you come from?\nYou never stop and rest\n\n河流啊\n我只有一個問題\nOh, river\nI have only one question \n\n你從哪裡來?\n你從不停歇嗎?\nWhere do you come from?\nYou never stop and rest\n', 91, '', 'Hemanta Kumar Mukhopadhyay', 'Hemanta Kumar Mukhopadhyay', '', '大大樹音樂圖像', '', 1, 1, 0, '2014-07-07 14:58:20', '2015-03-12 14:07:52', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
