(77265, 1892, 6411, 1, 'Kolkata 加爾各答', '音景:  2012-2013年加爾各答舊城、塔壩\n            1996年塔壩皮業工會抗議關廠遊行\nSoundscape: Recorded in Tangra and the old “Chinatown” of Kolkata 2012-2013,  and in 1996 at a protest by Tangra tannery workers and owners\n加爾各答街上放縱的聲響，無所節制的音量已成日常，或引人墜入迷幻狀態的噪樂。街聲無法遮掩地貫穿全片，最終成為我們對這城市共有的風景記憶。\n\nThe streets of Kolkata teem with unfettered sounds and noise that flow in a relentless, ceaseless stream, capable of inducing one to believe they are trapped in a dream or hallucination. This recording contains sounds that have been permanently etched in our memories of the city, and also includes footage from a march by leather factory workers in 1996.  They were protesting the closure of tanneries in Tangra, which were the source of livelihood for the Hakka Chinese there, who owned the factories and employed Indian workers.    ', '2014-07-23 00:00:00', 2000, 25, 0, 7, '', '', 114, '', '', '', '鍾適芳', '大大樹音樂圖像', '', 1, 1, 0, '2014-07-07 14:48:15', '2015-03-12 14:07:52', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(77266, 1892, 6411, 3, 'Cheena Para 中國街', '音景：流浪吟唱人（Baul）、加爾各答舊中國區中山街 \n音樂：Wolfgang Obrecht \nSoundscape:  Singing by a Baul minstrel; Sounds from Sun Yat-sen Street in Kolkata''s old Chinatown.\nMusic by Wolfgang Obrecht\n\n加爾各答舊中國區的風華雖將褪盡，街市小販仍叫賣著華人生活痕跡的證物，包子、餃子、魚丸湯、葉菜、廣東臘腸。流浪吟唱人（Baul）的流浪之歌，應和著華人的流離，是影片中試圖以聲音描繪的場景。\nStreet vendors who sell steamed dumplings and Cantonese sausage are the only remaining traces of the faded glory of Kolkata''s old Chinatown. In the film, we used the singing of a Baul minstrel to try and tap into the feelings of isolation and loneliness experienced by the Chinese diaspora in India. \n', '2014-07-23 00:00:00', 2000, 25, 0, 7, '', '', 66, '', '', '', '鍾適芳', '大大樹音樂圖像', '', 1, 1, 0, '2014-07-07 14:52:23', '2015-03-12 14:07:52', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(77267, 1892, 6411, 4, 'Light 光', '曲、演奏：Wolfgang Obrecht    \nWritten and performed by Wolfgang Obrecht\n故事從兩百多年前說起，傳說中第一個落腳加爾各答的華人。影片穿越沈重的時代記憶，1930、1947、1962，似光一般流轉到今日印度華人的生活樣貌。\n\n\nWritten in response to a 200-year-old legend of the first Chinese person to come to Kolkata. The film covers pivotal historical events that affected the Chinese in India -- 1930 (when the independence movement gains momentum in India), 1947 (the end of British rule), and 1962 (a border dispute between China and India, which resulted in formal declarations of war) -- all of which have had a lasting impact on the lives of the Indian Chinese.  \n', '2014-07-23 00:00:00', 2000, 25, 0, 7, '', '', 59, '', 'Wolfgang Obrecht ', '', '鍾適芳', '大大樹音樂圖像', '', 1, 1, 0, '2014-07-07 14:52:55', '2015-03-12 14:07:52', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(77268, 1892, 6411, 5, 'Azan 拜贊', '音景：加爾各答Chitpur街  \nSoundscape: Chitpur Street, Kolkata\n\n\n週五早上，當Azan迴旋，穆斯林穿戴整齊，匆匆穿越街巷，集合在加爾各答舊城清真寺四週。一列列信徒，沿街跪拜行禮，看不見隊伍的盡頭。\nFriday morning, on Chitupur Street in Kolkata, one hears the Azan, or the Islamic call to prayer. Dressed in long robes, worshippers fill the streets and alleys. Row after row, there is no visible end of devotees in sight.  \n', '2014-07-23 00:00:00', 2000, 25, 0, 7, '', '', 58, '', '', '', '鍾適芳', '大大樹音樂圖像', '', 1, 1, 0, '2014-07-07 14:54:29', '2015-03-12 14:07:52', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(77269, 1892, 6411, 7, 'Where I Came From 家', '曲、演奏：鍾玉鳳 Written and performed by Chung Yufeng\n\n對多數的印度華人來說，家既不是那個祖先來自的起點，也不是未知的終站，印度像是他們的家，又不是家。\nFor many Indian Chinese, "home" is not necessarily where their ancestors come from, nor is it not an unknown, foreign place. They call India "home," although at times it does not feel like a permanent home.\n', '2014-07-23 00:00:00', 2000, 25, 0, 7, '', '', 211, '', '鍾玉鳳', '', '鍾適芳', '大大樹音樂圖像', '', 1, 1, 0, '2014-07-07 14:55:12', '2015-03-12 14:07:52', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(77270, 1892, 6411, 8, 'From Border to Border (Independent Era) 邊界到邊界：獨立時代', '曲：鍾玉鳳\n演奏：Wolfgang Obrecht\nWritten by Chung Yufeng\nPerformed on accordion by Wolfgang Obrecht\n\n\n手風琴層疊反覆著時代的變動，行走在歷史中的人，卻不知道自己為什麼會在那樣的巨變下移動。\nHistory is kind to some, cruel to others. Several generations of Chinese in India fall in the latter category.  \n', '2014-07-23 00:00:00', 2000, 25, 0, 7, '', '', 55, '', '', '', '鍾適芳', '大大樹音樂圖像', '', 1, 1, 0, '2014-07-07 14:55:42', '2015-03-12 14:07:52', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(77271, 1892, 6411, 9, 'Paradise and Earth 天上人間', '詞：楊彥歧  曲：姚敏 \n演唱：萬芳\nLyrics by Yang Yan-chi, Composed by Yao Min\nPerformed by Wan Fang (Courtesy of hervoice)\nOP -  EMI MUSIC PUBLISHING HONG KONG\nSP -  EMI MUSIC PUBLISHING (S.E.ASIA) LTD.,TAIWAN  \n\n加爾各答舊城區向東行的塔壩，是客家人建立起的皮業聚落，市集供應著生活所需，新鮮的葉菜、油條、鹹煎餅、米糕、燒豬肉，公共廣播交替流轉著台灣時代曲、中國紅歌。拍攝中，廣播傳出「天上人間」，像是為塔壩的百年史配樂。每一代移民都在尋找他們的「天上人間」。萬芳慷慨地為影片試唱了多個版本。\n\n\nTangra, located in in east Kolkata, was once a major locale for leather tanneries run by the Hakka Chinese. Here one finds the offerings typical at a Chinese market: fresh bok choy, fried dough sticks, dumplings, rice cake, braised pork. While shooting footage for From Border to Border, we heard the song Paradise and Earth playing on a radio, and it felt as if this Chinese pop classic was telling the story of Tangra over the past hundred years. Immigrants everywhere seek their own "Paradise" on earth, and singer Wan Fang by generously offering her own rendition for the film soundtrack. \n', '2014-03-31 00:00:00', 2000, 25, 2, 7, '', '', 184, '', '姚敏', '楊彥歧', '', '大大樹音樂圖像', '', 1, 1, 0, '2014-07-07 14:57:03', '2015-03-12 14:07:52', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(77272, 1892, 6411, 12, 'Journey 旅程', '曲、演奏：Wolfgang Obrecht\nMusic written and performed by Wolfgang Obrecht\n\n\n對於上一代的印度華人來說，每一次啓程，都把他們帶向未知。 \nFor many older generations of Indian Chinese, every time they embark on a new journey, they are often brought to unknown places.\n', '2014-07-23 00:00:00', 2000, 25, 0, 7, '', '', 83, '', 'Wolfgang Obrecht', '', '鍾適芳', '大大樹音樂圖像', '', 1, 1, 0, '2014-07-07 14:57:40', '2015-03-12 14:07:52', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(77273, 1892, 6411, 13, 'O Nodi Re (Oh, River) 河流', '曲、詞、演唱：Hemanta Kumar Mukhopadhyay\nWritten and performed by Hemanta Kumar Mukhopadhyay\nSoundtrack from Under the Blue Sky (Courtesy of Mrinal Sen)   \n \n與薩也吉雷齊名的印度導演Mrinal Sen，1950年代拍攝的「藍色天空下」，以1930年代反殖氣氛湧動的加爾各答為背景，當時在加城巷弄間叫賣的山東絲綢小販也被刻畫其中。「藍色天空下」成為印度電影史上少數正面呈現華人形象，並著墨其內心的影片。製作人也是電影配樂的作曲、原唱Hemanta Kumar Mukhopadhyay，隨影片流動的歌聲讓人印象深刻。「河流」一曲，加深了當時華人被迫離鄉、印度被外人殖民的悲愁。借用了Mrinal Sen的故事與歌，與「邊界移動兩百年」的口述歷史交疊。 